500</td></tr></tbody></table></div>




<p></p>




<p></p>




<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>




<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US">These data are both skewed with=
 a sample size of n=3D7 in each treatment arm, and so a non-parametric test=
 is appropriate. Before we calculate the test, we choose a significance lev=
el (usually =CE=B1=3D0.05). The first step is to assign ranks to the values=
 from the full sample (both treatment groups pooled together) in order from=
 smallest to largest. We can then generate a test statistic based on the ra=
nks.</span></p>




<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US"><br></span></p>




<p>  </p>




